to the editor re health officials wield a big stick carefully against sars news article april 20 large scale quarantine has not been seen in north america since the 1920 's quarantine is not to be imposed lightly and does have serious consequences with sars we are still in the pre antibiotics era and rough and ready isolation may be of more than historical interest the request by ontario officials that potential sars patients stay home over easter weekend is not unprecedented similar precautions were instituted in response to the 1918 epidemic of spanish influenza james s bromberg md brookline mass april 21 2003

